Description: Papyrus containing 29 lines of Greek text on the recto and an illegible address on the verso. The text contains the sale of an female donkey for 600 drachmae.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (21985) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/21985)
Exhibition history: 2021-2022 25 Sep – 08 Oct, China, Suzhou Museum, 'Rome: City & Empire'
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Colgate Rochester Divinity School
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: P.Oxy. XIV 1707 (text edition abbreviation according to Oates et al 2001)
